29/12/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The cabinet approved a plan to fight corruption Thursday (December 28th) and forwarded it to parliament for consideration.
The plan contains some 168 recommendations on the implementation of a national strategy against corruption, including deadlines and initiatives to regulate anti-corruption measures.
In other news Thursday, the Roma Union of Serbia presented its election list to the Republican Electoral Commission.
The list includes 250 candidates for parliament.
Party leader Rajko Djuric stressed that this marks the first time a Roma minority party would independently participate in parliamentary elections, scheduled for January 21st.
(Politika, Blic - 29/12/06;
Tanjug - 28/12/06)
